worldVelocityOfBodyPoint

  • worldVelocityOfBodyPoint(bodyPoint: VectorE3): Vector
    • Defined in davinci-newton/engine/RigidBody.ts:178

    Returns dx/dt where

    dx/dt = ω x [R bodyPoint] + dX/dt (t argument suppressed)

    The implementation uses the angular velocity bivector, Ω = I * ω, where I is the unit pseudoscalar.

    Using the identity, ω x r = r << Ω, enables us to calculate directly.

    This method is most often used to calculate damping.

    Parameters

    • bodyPoint: VectorE3

    Returns Vector
